two cannot be understood without the context of go;
for myself, i take its release as a message to abandon the competitive sense i had built during the rise of one of the first real esports;
its previous lack of a recoil-following crosshair made out-of-game practice a requirement, even for casual play;
the only options were a huge time investment, or a terrible experience;
but now i can have a good time without feeling forced to 'git gud';
an endeavor i was always doomed to fail at, due to the timing of each round prohibiting flow states
